													"value": "A DNS firewall offers security and performance improvements for DNS servers by acting as a protective tool sitting between a user's resolver and the authoritative nameserver. It is equipped with rate-limiting capabilities to deter potential cyber attacks such as DoS and DDoS attacks. Some DNS firewalls offer the added benefit of improving performance.",
